Phase 3 is complete. Here's what I built and the decisions behind it.

## Frontend (the phase deliverable)

- **`src/api.ts`** — typed client mirroring the backend DTOs (`IdentifyRequest/Response`, `CreateReportRequest`, `DetailsRequest`, `ReportResponse`), with an `ApiError` and thin `api.identify / createReport / updateDetails / getReport` methods over `/api/*`.
- **`src/ReportContext.tsx`** — holds the active report in memory so Step 2 can read its id/checklist.
- **Routes** (`react-router-dom` v6, added): `/` identity gate, `/details` Step 1, `/checklist` (minimal Step-2 landing so **Next** has a destination and `checklist-PPE_01` is visible — full interaction is Phase 4).
- **Identity gate** — Name / Employee ID / Designation + Continue. `resume:false` creates a draft and goes to Details; `resume:true` shows the "We found a saved report from {updated_at}…" banner with Resume / Start new, plus the amber mismatch note when `mismatchWarning` is set.
- **Details step** — segmented buttons for report type (7), shift (A/B/C/G), category, severity; location/date/time/description/corrective/HOD/reporter fields; **Save** (PUT, toast "Saved", stay) and **Next** (PUT, navigate). Form re-seeds from the loaded report, so resume restores field values.
- **Compact styling** (`App.css`): tight spacing, inline segmented controls, progress header `Identity → Details → Checklist`.

All the required `data-testid`s match the contract in `orchestrator/e2e/tests/helpers.ts` exactly, and I traced my code against all four `phase3_gate_details.spec.ts` scenarios.

## Backend changes I had to make (flagged for your awareness)

The Phase 2 backend didn't match the Phase 3 / E2E contract, so the frontend couldn't have worked without these — all minimal:

1. **`ReportType`** realigned to the 7 spec values (`NEAR_MISS, UNSAFE_ACT, UNSAFE_CONDITION, FIRE_INCIDENT, PERMIT_TO_WORK, BEHAVIOUR_BASED, SAFETY_VIOLATION`). The old enum had `FIRST_AID_CASE/INCIDENT/ENVIRONMENTAL`, which would have 400'd.
2. **`ReporterCategory`** → `STAFF, CONTRACTOR, OTHER, VISITOR` (added `OTHER`, dropped unused `EMPLOYEE`).
3. **`DetailsRequest` + `updateDetails`** extended to persist `hodComments` and `reporterName` — the phase lists these as Details fields and requires Save to persist them; the columns and `ReportResponse` already supported them, only the request DTO omitted them.
4. **`tsconfig.node.json`** (scaffold defect) was missing `composite: true` and disabled emit, breaking `tsc -b`; fixed so `npm run build` passes.

No DB migration needed — those columns are plain `VARCHAR` with no CHECK constraints.

